article.description: Brittany Rayburn tied a career high with 22 points, and Purdue (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) snapped a three-game losing streak with an 82-65 win over Iona on Saturday night.
article.headline: Rayburn ties career high as Boilermakers roll
article.linkText: Rayburn's 22 help No. 23 Purdue stop skid
article.story:
WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. --Brittany Rayburn tied a career high with 22 points, and Purdue (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) snapped a three-game losing streak with an 82-65 win over Iona on Saturday night.

Jodi Howell scored 17 points, Lakisha Freeman had 11 and Danielle Campbell and FahKara Malone each added 10 for the Boilermakers (6-4). Lindsay Wisdom-Hylton, Purdue's leading scorer, finished with just five points, but she grabbed 13 rebounds. Malone had nine assists.

Thazina Cook and Anda Ivkovic each scored 18 points to lead Iona (8-3).

Purdue made 11-of-21 3-pointers, while Iona made 9-of-20. Howell made 5-of-6 3-pointers in the first half to help Purdue take a 43-30 lead.
